title: How have rates of timely antenatal assessments changed?
analysis_commentary: The ratio of women who had their first antenatal assessment before 12 weeks and six days has generally increased over time, from 2009/10 Q3 (87%) to 2014/15 Q3 (102%). For details on how this ratio can be higher than 100% please see 'about this data' at the bottom of this page.
